# <%= appName %> — Secrets for <%= provider %>

Environment: **<%= environment %>**

## Required environment variables (local)

Set these in your shell or CI before deploying:

<% if (provider === 'railway') { -%>
- `RAILWAY_TOKEN` — Railway API token
<% } else if (provider === 'fly') { -%>
- `FLY_API_TOKEN` — Fly.io API token
<% } else if (provider === 'aws') { -%>
- `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID`
- `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`
<% } else if (provider === 'gcp') { -%>
- `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS` — path to service account JSON
<% } else if (provider === 'azure') { -%>
- `AZURE_CLIENT_ID`
- `AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET`
- `AZURE_TENANT_ID`
<% } else if (provider === 'vercel') { -%>
- `VERCEL_TOKEN`
<% } else if (provider === 'netlify') { -%>
- `NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN`
<% } else if (provider === 'render') { -%>
- `RENDER_API_KEY`
<% } else if (provider === 'digitalocean') { -%>
- `DIGITALOCEAN_ACCESS_TOKEN`
<% } -%>

## Sync local secrets

```bash
my deploy secrets sync --provider <%= provider %> --dry-run
my deploy secrets sync --provider <%= provider %>
```
